webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Undated Winter Image from Nykvarn in Lköpping. At the quay, the engine cargo ship Rengen is seen. The boat was originally built as a barge at Lköpping’s shipyard in 1919, and was probably the last major ship built in the city. The name Rengen got the boat in 1924. In the past, she was one of the five so-called AGE barges, the last in the order AGE 5. The transport facility that glimpses into the background belongs to Lköpping’s Wooden Processing Plant - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240124. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021017430165. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
